****************************************************************
* Installation of dynamic library based versions of XPCE.
****************************************************************

Preliminaries:
==============

Install SWI-Prolog 2.0.10 or later.  The sources may be obtained from

	ftp://swi.psy.uva.nl/pub/SWI-Prolog/pl-2.1.0.tar.gz

Binaries for various architectures are   in  subdirecties indicating the
machine.

Unpacking:
==========

	% cd <to SWI-Prolog main directory (/usr/local/lib/pl-<plversion>)>
	% gunzip xpcebin-<version>-for-<machine>.tgz | tar xf -
	% gunzip xpcelib-<version> | tar xf -

Will create xpce-<version> directory in the prolog home directory

Installation:
=============

	% ln -s xpce-<version> xpce
	% cp xpce/pl/src/plrc .
	% cd <public binary directory>
	% ln -s pl xpce

Notes for various machines:
===========================

	* Sparc-sunos-4.1.3:
	  ==================

	Dynamic linked version has the following dynamic dependencies
	
	-lXt.4 => /usr/lib/libXt.so.4.10
        -lX11.4 => /usr/lib/libX11.so.4.10
        -ldl.1 => /usr/lib/libdl.so.1.0
        -lc.1 => /usr/lib/libc.so.1.8

	The X11 libraries are from the MIT X11R5 distribution.  If you
	are using another version of these libraries, you may wish to
	grab ../X11R5-sparc-sunos-4.1.3.tgz, containing

	-rw-r--r-- root/staff   294912 Dec 12 17:58 1991 lib/libXt.so.4.10
	-rw-r--r-- root/staff   442368 Dec 12 17:57 1991 lib/libX11.so.4.10

	These files must be installed in one of the directories searched
	by ld.so (/usr/lib or a directory of the LD_LIBRARY_PATH variable).

	* Sparc-sunos-5.4:
	  ================

	Dynamic linked version of xpce4pl.so has the following dependencies:

	ldd pl/sparc-solaris2.4/xpce4pl.so
        libXt.so.4 =>    /usr/openwin/lib/libXt.so.4
        libX11.so.4 =>   /usr/openwin/lib/libX11.so.4
        libucb.so.1 =>   /usr/ucblib/libucb.so.1
        libresolv.so.1 =>        /usr/lib/libresolv.so.1
        libsocket.so.1 =>        /usr/lib/libsocket.so.1
        libnsl.so.1 =>   /usr/lib/libnsl.so.1
        libelf.so.1 =>   /usr/lib/libelf.so.1
        libXext.so.0 =>  /usr/openwin/lib/libXext.so.0
        libc.so.1 =>     /usr/lib/libc.so.1
        libdl.so.1 =>    /usr/lib/libdl.so.1
        libw.so.1 =>     /usr/lib/libw.so.1
        libintl.so.1 =>  /usr/lib/libintl.so.1
